# Repository documentation boundary:
# - Maintainer-facing repository docs are commit/upload eligible when curated to
#   explain project structure, execution roadmaps, function maps, or maintenance
#   decisions (for example: Architecture/ExecutionRoadmap.md,
#   Architecture/ExecutionRoadMap.md, FUNCTION_MAP.md). The authoritative
#   FunctionMap location is the root uppercase `FUNCTION_MAP.md`; avoid
#   case-conflicting or duplicate FunctionMap files.
# - `REQUIREMENTS_TRACEABILITY.md` is local-only and forbidden from upload.
# - Local-only temporary engineering/audit artifacts stay excluded until they are
#   intentionally converted into maintainer-facing documentation.
# - Do not ignore a broad Docs/ directory: Windows case-insensitive matching can
#   also hide curated lowercase docs/. Use the specific scratch/private patterns
#   below for local-only notes instead.
EXTERNAL_PROJECT_ANALYSIS.md
failure_inventory.md
*_plan_draft*.md
*_planning_draft*.md
*_audit_dump*.md
*_audit_dump*.json
*_audit_log*.md
*_audit_log*.jsonl
*_scratch*.md
*_scratch_notes*.md
*_machine_notes*.md
*_codex_notes*.md
*_codex_cache*.md
*_gap-analysis*.md
*_gap_analysis*.md
*_private_analysis*.md
*_transient_checklist*.md
*_uncurated_engineering*.md
*_validation_notes*.md
